      • GaussFloat

        public GaussFloat(double[] sigma,
                  RandomAccessible<FloatType> input,
                  Interval interval,
                  ImgFactory<FloatType> factory)
        Deprecated. 
        Computes a Gaussian convolution with float precision on a RandomAccessible of FloatType in a certain Interval and returns an Img defined by the ImgFactory containing the result
        Parameters:
        sigma - - the sigma for the convolution
        input - - the RandomAccessible to work on
        interval - - the area that is convolved
        factory - - the ImgFactory that defines the temporary and output images to be used

      • GaussFloat

        public GaussFloat(double[] sigma,
                  RandomAccessible<FloatType> input,
                  Interval interval,
                  RandomAccessible<FloatType> output,
                  Localizable outputOffset,
                  ImgFactory<FloatType> factory)
        Deprecated. 
        Computes a Gaussian convolution with float precision on a RandomAccessible of FloatType in a certain Interval and writes it into a given RandomAccessible at a specific Point
        Parameters:
        sigma - - the sigma for the convolution
        input - - the RandomAccessible to work on
        interval - - the area that is convolved
        output - - the RandomAccessible where the output will be written to
        outputOffset - - the offset that corresponds to the first pixel in output RandomAccessible
        factory - - the ImgFactory for creating temporary images

      • processLine

        protected void processLine(SamplingLineIterator<FloatType> input,
                           double[] kernel)
        Deprecated. 
        Compute the current line. It is up to the implementation howto really do that. The idea is to only iterate over the input once (that's why it is an Iterator) as it is potentially an expensive operation (e.g. a Converter might be involved or we are computing on a rendered input)
        Overrides:
        processLine in class AbstractGauss<FloatType>
        Parameters:
        input - - the Iterator/Sampler over the current input line.
